To fix the "Row-Level Security (RLS)" upload error, please run the following SQL code in your **Supabase SQL Editor**. This gives your website permission to actually put files into the buckets you created.

### 1. SQL Code for Permissions
```sql
-- ENABLE UPLOADS FOR BLOG IMAGES
CREATE POLICY "Public Blog Upload" ON storage.objects FOR INSERT TO public WITH CHECK (bucket_id = 'blog-images');
CREATE POLICY "Public Blog Update" ON storage.objects FOR UPDATE TO public WITH CHECK (bucket_id = 'blog-images');
CREATE POLICY "Public Blog Select" ON storage.objects FOR SELECT TO public USING (bucket_id = 'blog-images');
CREATE POLICY "Public Blog Delete" ON storage.objects FOR DELETE TO public USING (bucket_id = 'blog-images');

-- ENABLE UPLOADS FOR PROPERTY IMAGES
CREATE POLICY "Public Property Upload" ON storage.objects FOR INSERT TO public WITH CHECK (bucket_id = 'property-images');
CREATE POLICY "Public Property Update" ON storage.objects FOR UPDATE TO public WITH CHECK (bucket_id = 'property-images');
CREATE POLICY "Public Property Select" ON storage.objects FOR SELECT TO public USING (bucket_id = 'property-images');
CREATE POLICY "Public Property Delete" ON storage.objects FOR DELETE TO public USING (bucket_id = 'property-images');
```

### 2. UI Reversion & Fixes
I have completely restructured the **AdminPostForm** to match the **WordPress Classic Editor** layout exactly as you specified:
*   **Main Column**: Title -> Permalink (Slug) -> Editor -> Excerpt -> SEO Keyphrase -> Meta Description.
*   **Sidebar**: Publish Box -> Featured Image Box -> Categories Box.

