To fix the "new row violates row-level security policy" error and update the editor tools as requested, follow these two steps:

### 1. SQL Code for Supabase
Run this in your **Supabase SQL Editor** to grant your website permission to upload images. This resolves the RLS (Row-Level Security) error.

```sql
-- Allow the website to upload and manage images in the required buckets
CREATE POLICY "Public Insert" ON storage.objects FOR INSERT TO public WITH CHECK (bucket_id IN ('property-images', 'blog-images'));
CREATE POLICY "Public Select" ON storage.objects FOR SELECT TO public USING (bucket_id IN ('property-images', 'blog-images'));
CREATE POLICY "Public Update" ON storage.objects FOR UPDATE TO public WITH CHECK (bucket_id IN ('property-images', 'blog-images'));
CREATE POLICY "Public Delete" ON storage.objects FOR DELETE TO public USING (bucket_id IN ('property-images', 'blog-images'));
```

